James on Instagram: "Still deeply in the changing-the-strap-every-few-hours phase with the @bremontwatches S302 GMT. For this outing, I figured I would borrow some inspiration from the latest Bond watch (which shares coloring with the S302). I bought a $22 (CAD) 20mm mesh bracelet from a brand called Maker. I like the look, design (sliding adjustment and quick change bars), and price of this mesh but it was only offered in a polished finish. I opted for a DIY route and used a fine sanding block to brush away that flashy finish. I think it looks great and rather suits the watch, though admittedly the steel of the bracelet is a bit brighter than the case. All in all, a great bracelet option for the money."

Anchor text: Jason’s Auction of the Doxa Sub 300 Divingstar Poseidon edition
Title: Jason Heaton on Instagram: "*FINAL BID - $5,500! A DOXA watch auction for a good cause! If you’ve followed or known me for any length of time, you know that Sri Lanka is my adopted second home and my wife’s birthplace. You might also know that Sri Lanka is hurting more than ever before. The country’s economic crisis has created fuel shortages, power outages, scarcity of medicines, and food shortages. So I’ve decided to offer my Doxa SUB 300T Divingstar Poseidon to the highest bidder, with ALL proceeds of the sale going to provide lunches to schoolchildren. I’m working with the Nugegoda Children’s Meal Club. For a mere 170 rupees (about 50 cents US currently), they can provide a lunch for a child and with help from the sale of this watch, their support can be multiplied many times over and grow beyond their current schools. This makes a HUGE difference at the most basic level with no administrative overhead. The program is being overseen by a friend of ours (@tinajourno ) on the ground in Sri Lanka. The watch is an un-numbered pre-production Doxa SUB 300T Divingstar on bracelet, with extra links and a new ISOfrane rubber strap. For appropriate provenance, this watch has been underwater off the east coast of Sri Lanka. It is in good running shape, but has a few marks from regular wear. The production run of this watch was 500 pieces back in 2018, in partnership with the legendary Swedish dive gear company, Poseidon. Neither Doxa nor Poseidon has any involvement with this auction. It will come packaged in a Doxa aluminum tube with the extra links and rubber strap but since it was not a production watch, it did not come with a manual or warrantee card.  To bid, simply add a comment to this Instagram post. I’ll try to update the latest bid at the top of the description as often as I can but be sure to check comments for the latest high bid. Bidding will close on Monday, September 12th at 12 noon, Central US Time, with funds to be collected as soon as possible (to be arranged privately). After that, I will ship the watch anywhere FedEx delivers at my own expense, but the winner must pay any import duties if it’s outside the USA. Thanks in advance for your interest and happy bidding!"

Cole Pennington on Instagram: "Two things to get on your radar: JDM trucks and the NJ Pine Barrens! We’ll start with the Pinelands. It’s just over two hours from NYC but it feels like you’ve travelled to the PNW. This ecosystem is even home to orchids. It’s beautiful and totally worth checking out. It’s best to take a truck that’s capable and get deep into it. There are plenty of trails. That brings me to the second item. This Mitsubishi Pajero is straight from Japan, right hand drive at all. Here’s why I chose it: It’s turbodiesel, manual, has 4WD with factory locking diff, it costs less than $10K, seats 7, CRUSHES the trails, and has a stout little 2.5 liter that’s torquey enough to get through those holes. MPG is solid, too. I started the search for a truck two years ago for something that’s manual, turbodiesel, and 4WD. There are plenty of 🇺🇸 trucks that meet those parameters but they’re pricey. I was looking for something 10K max. JDM is where the value is at. Furthermore, you don’t have to get it inspected, at least in NJ. #drivetastefully #offroadnation #overland #fromwhereiride #pinebarrens #pajero"

Jason Heaton on Instagram: "Watch for Good! This is an auction, with 100% of the winning bid to be donated to Big Brothers Big Sisters of America. 15 years ago, @gishanir and I became mentors in the local Big Brothers Big Sisters program and were matched with an 11-year old boy from a difficult home situation. Over the subsequent years, our relationship developed into one of the richest experiences of our lives. We are still friends with this confident, polite and strong African-American man and I dare say we gained as much, if not more, from the whole experience as he did. It taught us about African-American culture, how to get through difficult situations, how to stretch comfort levels, and the meaning of true friendship across generations and cultures. Given the current situation in America, I strongly feel that bridging divides of age, race, cultures, and socioeconomic levels is more important than ever and I’d like to help keep that going. The watch in question is a Unimatic U1-DZ, one of only 400 made. It has a 41mm steel case water resistant to 300 meters, sports a rotating 12-hour bezel, and runs a Seiko NH35A automatic movement. The watch is fitted with an excellent nylon NATO strap and comes with a second, camouflage rubber pass-through strap, both with Unimatic signed buckles. Boxes and warrantee card included. The watch is in excellent condition and runs well. The auction is fully endorsed by Unimatic, but please direct all questions about the watch to me. Following on the successful auction recently run by @garactacle , I’m borrowing his format (thanks, @garactacle ): Auction timeframe: Auction is open as of this posting, and will end at Noon CDT, Friday, June 12th.  Opening Bid: $200 Bidding increment: $50 or more. To keep the highest possible amount for donation, $30 will be added to the final price if the shipping address is outside the United States. How to bid: Submit your bid via comment on this post, and this post only. DO NOT reply to someone else’s bid. DO NOT DM, email or comment on stories or other posts. You can bid multiple times till the end time. Good luck and thank you! #watchforgood"

Nirmal Purja MBE - NIMSDAI on Instagram: ".I hear it 🙌🏽🙏.Certainly there has been a lot of debate , critics, and the blaming games about this pic which I took on Everest this year.( I know many big news agency didn’t gave the RIGHT CREDENTIALS) .Both climbers coming up and going down wanted to have the priority. Somebody had to step up to solve this issue or otherwise it was gonna go chaotic. I have never been phased out by the problems at extreme high altitude or in the operations I have been during my Special Forces Career. In-fact, I get outmost satisfaction in problem solving. I was there managing the traffic for almost 90 minutes. Point to note , nobody lost their life or had and issues whilst we were there. I strongly believe that the nature is for everyone and it’s not only for the rich and only who can afford. I personally think and belive  the cost of the permits should remain the same. This issues of over crowding can easily be resolved if the fixed lines are set before the end of April so the climbers have full month ( May ) to chose and pick when they would like to summit with much more leeway to play about. To those who are thinking of climbing Everest in the future; please don’t take short cuts for your own safety ! If I’m honest, I do acclimatise a lot quicker than most of the human beings but when I first started mountaineering career in 2012: I started with ticking off 6000m then 7000m then 8000m peaks to experience how my body would react at those altitude.
